  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Regional MSME Investment Fund for Sub-Saharan Africa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Regional MSME Investment Fund for Sub-Saharan Africa (REGMIFA or the fund) is a proposed collective debt investment vehicle to support micro and small businesses in Sub-Saharan Africa. The objectives of REGMIFA are (i) to offer and encourage additional but market-based financing  with an emphasis on local currency  to financial entities serving micro and small businesses (microfinance institutions or MFIs; (ii) to help establish microfinance as an asset class with mainstream investors and leverage donor funds with private capital; and (iii) to support medium-term capacity building among financial entities serving micro and small businesses. REGMIFA will provide local currency debt financing to smaller banks, non-bank institutions and commercially oriented NGOs that serve small and micro businesses. A parallel TA facility will provide capacity building support to investees.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project is expected to contribute to employment creation and poverty reduction in Sub-Saharan Africa. Specifically, it will contribute to the development and growth of the microfinance sector in the region and enable better access to finance for an estimated 100,000 micro and small businesses over the next five years. The project will also contribute to the establishment of microfinance as an asset class, which will encourage further private sector financing being provided to the sector.</narrative>
  </description>
